result.text: Trump’s repeated use of the word “reserve” initially excited Bitcoin supporters, who thought it meant the government would buy more Bitcoin. However, the order clarifies that no new purchases are planned right now. Instead, the government will focus on organizing the crypto it already owns. That said, the order allows the Treasury and Commerce Departments to explore ways to buy more Bitcoin or altcoins in the future, but only if it doesn’t cost taxpayers extra money.
